00:10:38,447 --> 00:10:41,768
Be it resolved that the monthly taking

124
00:10:42,323 --> 00:10:52,126
since December of 2013 by the city administration of Comcast and Verizon ratepayers for public access TV be discussed.

125
00:10:52,307 --> 00:10:52,987
Councillor Pinto.

126
00:10:53,127 --> 00:11:00,029
Mr. President, since 2013 until now, December of 2015, it's been approximately 2 years.

127
00:11:01,390 --> 00:11:10,853
And during that period of time, the city of Medford has intentionally, the city administration has intentionally taken ratepayers' money from Comcast and subsequently, since Verizon has come on board,

128
00:11:11,443 --> 00:11:14,004
for what they call public access TV here in the city of Medford.

129
00:11:14,604 --> 00:11:24,027
As of today, there is approximately $400,000, $450,000 sitting in the city coffers downstairs for public access television.

130
00:11:24,607 --> 00:11:31,369
Public access television for which the mayor and its current administration has intentionally not allowed here in the city of Medford.

131
00:11:32,090 --> 00:11:33,250
And who's at the loss of that?

132
00:11:33,370 --> 00:11:35,031
And that's the cable TV subscribers.

133
00:11:35,631 --> 00:11:39,592
Whether you agree or disagree with anyone running for office, no candidate

134
00:11:39,922 --> 00:11:47,026
for this past election had the opportunity to be on public access, to have their position stated, accepted, rejected, or even looked at.

135
00:11:47,926 --> 00:11:58,232
No citizen of this community has had the opportunity to have their shows relative to sports, family events, or anything that might be educational, historical, to be put on public access television.

136
00:11:58,832 --> 00:12:07,677
During the past two years, what the mayor did is he implemented a three-member committee person, three-member person committee, for the purposes of reviewing public access here in the city of Medford.

137
00:12:08,317 --> 00:12:09,798
Coming up with a concocted story,

138
00:12:10,165 --> 00:12:16,428
that at some point in time, on or before Memorial Day of 2015, we would have something ongoing.

139
00:12:16,768 --> 00:12:17,289
And we don't.

140
00:12:17,349 --> 00:12:20,970
This is now December 2015, almost seven months later.

141
00:12:21,791 --> 00:12:28,034
And the money just keeps coming out of your cable bill each and every month from Verizon and Comcast.

142
00:12:28,674 --> 00:12:34,077
We had a public access meeting here for contract renewal with Comcast here in the city of Medford.

143
00:12:34,577 --> 00:12:36,298
It was another 10-year deal.

144
00:12:37,139 --> 00:12:39,680
And no one, not one person from the city administration,

145
00:12:40,087 --> 00:12:44,931
Not one person showed up to defend and argue on behalf of Comcast customers.

146
00:12:45,572 --> 00:12:48,074
I, along with nine other citizens, were here to do that.

147
00:12:48,634 --> 00:12:50,836
And this isn't because we're for or against.

148
00:12:51,297 --> 00:12:52,518
It's a 10-year contract.

149
00:12:52,578 --> 00:13:00,224
And in today's day and age, 10-year contracts are basically unheard of, especially when technology is so far advanced and it's ever-changing.

150
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:06,550
From California all the way to Massachusetts, there's a combination of maybe even a collage

151
00:13:07,092 --> 00:13:14,678
between Verizon and Comcast technicians working together, sharing their jobs together as they traverse across the country.

152
00:13:15,178 --> 00:13:33,211
And yes, there is a movement out there that maybe public access is not the way to go because between Amazon and all these other technological programs that are out there between a combination of streaming or buying on Netflix or whatever it might be, the idea is out there that the city of Medford is not having it.

153
00:13:33,731 --> 00:13:36,293
With a proposal now that seems to be languishing,

154
00:13:36,642 --> 00:13:43,905
of possibly putting it up in the vocational school, a place that would serve no purpose, especially in the winter months that we have right now.

155
00:13:44,445 --> 00:13:45,245
It's dark out.

156
00:13:45,625 --> 00:13:48,687
The bus route would stop the person getting off at the bottom of the hill.

157
00:13:48,727 --> 00:13:50,487
You would have to walk up to the top of the hill.

158
00:13:50,527 --> 00:13:53,208
God knows where you would have to go into the building to get in.

159
00:13:53,728 --> 00:14:02,011
It does not serve a purpose because all this type of information on public access needs to be located in a centrally located place.

160
00:14:02,552 --> 00:14:06,013
And when you have something that's centrally located, it would bring more people.

161
00:14:06,645 --> 00:14:09,467
City of Reading, Town of Reading, perfect example.

162
00:14:09,507 --> 00:14:14,011
Not only do they have it in the downtown area, they have it on every Saturday morning at 11 o'clock.

163
00:14:14,051 --> 00:14:15,712
It's open to the public, coffee and donuts.

164
00:14:15,992 --> 00:14:16,713
People can come in.

165
00:14:17,053 --> 00:14:18,694
They show you how to make your own program.

166
00:14:18,734 --> 00:14:20,736
They lease out, rent out their equipment.

167
00:14:21,076 --> 00:14:22,377
They show you how to use the equipment.

168
00:14:22,397 --> 00:14:23,958
They show you how to make your own programs.

169
00:14:24,519 --> 00:14:27,121
I know we've had this discussion before over and over and over again.

170
00:14:27,541 --> 00:14:30,043
But the fact of the matter is when we started this discussion,

171
00:14:30,379 --> 00:14:34,842
There was nowhere near $450,000 sitting in the coffers downstairs.

172
00:14:35,463 --> 00:14:49,973
And when in fact some of that money was used to pay for salaries of three individuals up at the high school in a program out there that has nothing to do and has nothing to do by law with cable access and public TV access here in the city of Medford, and nothing's been challenged in that particular area.

173
00:14:50,553 --> 00:14:57,258
What needs to be done in this city is that you need a revolution in thought where people can turn around and say, hey, wait a minute.

174
00:14:58,193 --> 00:15:02,757
These are your dollars that are being taken out of your cable bill each and every month.

175
00:15:03,077 --> 00:15:04,718
It's almost like coming out of your check.

176
00:15:05,059 --> 00:15:06,880
You're paying for something that you're not getting.

177
00:15:06,900 --> 00:15:12,024
$450,000 is nothing to sneeze at, and you still have nothing for it.

178
00:15:12,604 --> 00:15:15,847
It's unfortunate that we have to talk about this thing over and over again.

179
00:15:16,107 --> 00:15:17,248
It's like the police station.

180
00:15:17,508 --> 00:15:18,588
There's a problem out there.

181
00:15:18,948 --> 00:15:19,989
It's being discussed.

182
00:15:20,309 --> 00:15:21,429
It needs to be discussed.

183
00:15:21,569 --> 00:15:25,331
It needs to be revolutionized to the point it needs change.

184
00:15:26,031 --> 00:15:28,292
New council coming in, new administration coming in.

185
00:15:28,712 --> 00:15:30,152
I hope the change takes effect.

186
00:15:30,933 --> 00:15:34,954
But the people, you, the taxpayers out there, you're paying for this each and every day.

187
00:15:35,434 --> 00:15:46,878
And you need to hold every one of the councils accountable, as well as the mayor, to make sure that your tax dollars, your cable bills, your water bills, anything that revolves around you paying for something in this community,

188
00:15:47,363 --> 00:15:51,786
for a service or a tax or a bill is being accounted for and spent wisely.

189
00:15:51,806 --> 00:16:14,262
I would hope, and I'll leave this as a thought rather than asking or putting the council on the spot, I would hope as a thought that the incoming city council does not allow this to continue to go on, that you come up and step up forward in demand of the new city administration, that you want cable access television here in the city of Medford.

190
00:16:14,702 --> 00:16:16,183
That's what the people have paid for.

191
00:16:16,802 --> 00:16:22,246
If not, give them the $450,000 back and figure out another way to do business here because it's absolutely wrong.

192
00:16:22,566 --> 00:16:26,969
It's almost stealing people's money and not doing what they're supposed to be doing with it.

193
00:16:27,509 --> 00:16:28,710
And that is just so wrong.

194
00:16:29,571 --> 00:16:34,434
You don't tell our kids when you're making them grow up, this is the way life is supposed to be.

195
00:16:34,674 --> 00:16:38,657
You pay for something you're not getting or you take something that you don't deserve.

196
00:16:38,677 --> 00:16:40,298
That's exactly what's happening.

197
00:16:40,859 --> 00:16:44,901
The city has taken your money that they don't deserve because they're not doing anything with it.

198
00:16:45,041 --> 00:16:45,802
And at the same time,

199
00:16:46,102 --> 00:16:47,843
You're paying for something that you're not getting.

200
00:16:48,703 --> 00:16:51,184
It's a no-win situation for you, the ratepayers.

201
00:16:51,905 --> 00:17:06,391
So with that being said, I would hope, Mr. President, and Rick, I know next year, I'm assuming if the deal is the way the deal is supposed to be, you as the president of the council, you would be able to tell, you know, this is where we're going to go with this particular direction.

202
00:17:06,932 --> 00:17:11,694
And as far as that goes, Mr. President, I leave my comments as they are.

203
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:12,454
Thank you.

204
00:17:12,494 --> 00:17:13,735
Chair recognizes Councilor Marks.

205
00:17:15,504 --> 00:17:16,504
Thank you, Mr. President.

206
00:17:16,624 --> 00:17:18,946
